<glossary>
<definition id="ch08mod02_gl01">
<term>marginal revenue</term>
<meaning id="ch08mod02_gl01m">the additional revenue gained from selling one more unit</meaning>    
</definition>
<definition id="ch08mod02_gl02">
<term>shutdown point</term>
<meaning id="ch08mod02_gl02m">level of output where the marginal cost curve intersects the average variable cost curve at the minimum point of AVC; if the price is below this point, the firm should shut down immediately</meaning>    
</definition>
